text.tspan: Motivated Social Worker with comprehensive knowledge of social justice issues and systems affecting
marginalized communities. Passionate about developing and facilitating programs to support
communities in need. Collaborative and analytical with proven ability to build strategic partnerships,
advocate for clients and advance change for communities in need.
Facilitate six individual and group therapy sessions per week to solve problems, set and
achieve goals and improve communication skills.
Coordinate individualized discharge plans to manage safe transition back into community and
Work with at-risk youth in residential facilities.
Developed treatments and casework programs for average of 37 patients each month.
Offered therapeutic services and crises intervention to emotionally disturbed children and
Facilitated supportive services and counseling for family members to address special concerns
and ease transition during home visits.
Coordinated psychosocial assessments, treatment plans and progress notes.
Managed caseload of 46 families and children in child welfare system.
